<a name="Instructure Canvas">
<h4>
1.5.6.  Instructure Canvas
</h4>
</a>
<p>
Instructure Canvas is a web-based learning management system (LMS) used
in all levels of education, K-12, as well as in higher ed. It is a all-round
management tool that supports features including but not limited to: grading, 
testing, discussions, collaborations, announcements, and instructor feedback.
</p>
<p>
<strong>Good Features:</strong>
<ul>
<li>Students can use all features for free with an account</li>
<li>Manages multiple classes for instructors and students</li>
<li>Sub-class level groups can be formed and managed</li>
<li>Manages student submissions of various formats</li>
<li>Students can easily access assignments, grades, and feedback</li>
<li>Supports a calendar view of all assignments and tests</li>

</ul>
<p>
<strong>Bad Features:</strong>
<ul>
<li>It relatively slow compared to other systems</li>
<li>Instructor or institurion needs to purchase an account</li>
<li>It only supports single-level, complex assignments</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Missing Features:</strong>
<ul>
<li>Spreadsheet style input interface that is enhanced for grading</li>
<li>Course grade curve adjustments</li>
<li>Student centered what if analysis</li>
<li>Integration with Cal Poly's authentication system</li>
<li>Graphical representation of class trend and individual grades</li>
</ul>


